I already got what I wanted.
What the fuck would we talk about?

27:02.845 --> 27:04.429
Say, Nucky,

27:04.480 --> 27:06.264
- about that thing.
- What thing?

27:06.315 --> 27:08.567
- The thing I wanted to talk to you about.
- Wait, I gotta get cigarettes.

27:31.290 --> 27:33.458
Nucky Thompson is here.

27:35.128 --> 27:37.963
Mr. Thompson,
what an honor.

27:38.014 --> 27:40.682
He was a good man.
My deepest condolences.

27:40.717 --> 27:43.752
I hadn't even realized
you knew my husband.

27:43.770 --> 27:47.556
Oh, of course. He was a fine fellow.
Just last month we spoke.

27:47.590 --> 27:49.691
Oh...

27:49.726 --> 27:51.476
But the laryngectomy.

28:08.544 --> 28:10.996
Fellas, meet the missus.

28:11.047 --> 28:12.798
She ain't much on personality,

28:12.832 --> 28:15.467
but she don't talk back none neither.

28:17.286 --> 28:19.788
What's the matter, kid,
never seen a stiff before?

28:19.806 --> 28:23.091
I've seen a couple.

28:24.811 --> 28:27.562
I'm short on time, Mickey.
What'd you want to show me?

28:27.597 --> 28:30.015
So much for the niceties.

28:49.502 --> 28:51.253
My factory, gentlemen.

28:51.287 --> 28:53.955
- Quite an operation.
- 10 shiners,

28:53.989 --> 28:56.124
two shifts, 24 hours a day...

28:56.158 --> 28:58.960
Gotta figure we're puttin' out
close to 2,000 crates a week.

28:58.994 --> 29:00.846
And that's just for starters.

29:00.880 --> 29:04.165
- None of this is legit?
- Not once they get through with it.

29:04.183 --> 29:06.101
One part real,
eight parts water.

29:06.135 --> 29:09.471
You heat it up, let it cool then add
your alcohol to bring up your proof.

29:09.505 --> 29:12.006
- Where do you get your alcohol?
- Potatoes.

29:12.024 --> 29:15.527
You let 'em ferment.
It smell's rough,

29:15.561 --> 29:17.813
but compared to a stiff,
it's fuckin' lilacs.

29:17.847 --> 29:19.781
After you add the alcohol,

29:19.816 --> 29:22.617
you throw in your caramel
coloring, your oil of rye,

29:22.652 --> 29:24.853
bourbon... depending
what you want.

29:24.871 --> 29:27.539
- You can make scotch too?
- Naturally.

29:27.573 --> 29:30.242
You just gotta add some
carbonyl though for the bead.

29:30.293 --> 29:32.694
- What's that?
- The bubbles.

29:32.712 --> 29:34.296
Higher the proof,

29:34.330 --> 29:36.498
more bead it's supposed
to have.

29:36.532 --> 29:38.583
Go on, bottoms up.

29:48.477 --> 29:51.346
- What the fuck's in this shit?
- Carbonyl, like I said.

29:51.380 --> 29:53.815
Formaldehyde.

29:53.850 --> 29:56.351
- Formaldehyde, huh?
- Hey hey hey hey!

29:56.385 --> 29:59.387
- What are you doing?
- Cocksucker!

30:06.829 --> 30:09.531
What the hell's wrong with you?
Out!

30:09.565 --> 30:11.065
Now! Beat it.

30:12.067 --> 30:14.920
Jimmy, out!

30:19.175 --> 30:22.043
- Stupid bohunk.
- It was just a gag, okay?

30:22.077 --> 30:25.380
- Yeah, you're a real pistol.
- Enough with the bohunk cracks.

30:25.414 --> 30:28.016
- My name's Doyle now.
- What?

30:28.050 --> 30:30.050
I changed it.
I ain't Mickey Cusick no more.

30:31.204 --> 30:34.206
- Who's after you?
- Nobody.

30:34.241 --> 30:37.409
- Then why Doyle?
- It sounds better is all.

30:37.443 --> 30:39.879
A rose by any other name.

30:39.913 --> 30:42.114
What's that supposed to mean?

30:42.132 --> 30:44.500
Read a fucking book.

30:47.954 --> 30:50.890
- What, are you off your nut?
- You didn't drink that piss, I did.

30:50.924 --> 30:53.309
- You're still breathing, aren't you?
- Yeah, so's he.

30:53.343 --> 30:55.427
That's the problem...
he's still breathing.

30:55.461 --> 30:58.814
- He's part of my operation, kid.
- You don't need him.

30:58.849 --> 31:01.267
What would you know about it?

31:01.301 --> 31:04.403
What's with you? And don't tell
me it's your goddamned stomach.

31:04.437 --> 31:06.572
You want to know what's with me?
Honestly?

31:06.606 --> 31:09.024
- Yeah.
- Paddy Ryan.

31:09.075 --> 31:11.944
You really expect me
to go work for that Mick?

31:11.978 --> 31:14.029
You'd rather be my driver?

31:14.080 --> 31:15.698
Of course not, Nuck.
It's just you...

31:15.749 --> 31:18.450
you make Ryan clerk?
I can run rings around that chump.

31:19.586 --> 31:21.653
Oh, listen to Bonnie
prince Charlie.

31:21.671 --> 31:24.323
C'mon, Nuck, you were assistant
sheriff when you were my age.

31:24.341 --> 31:27.877
And for eight years prior I spent night
and day kissing the commodore's ass.

31:27.928 --> 31:29.845
I've been kissing your ass
since I was 12!

31:29.880 --> 31:31.714
And what about
the last three years?

31:33.934 --> 31:35.551
I wanted to serve my country.

31:35.602 --> 31:37.853
- And nearly get yourself killed.
- Sssh.

31:37.888 --> 31:40.723
Did it ever occur how your
girl might feel about that?

31:40.774 --> 31:44.560
- Your little boy?
- Look, if that was my fate, then so be it.

31:44.611 --> 31:46.845
And he wants to be in politics.

31:46.863 --> 31:50.282
You know who dies for their country, kid?
Fucking rubes, that's who.

31:52.452 --> 31:54.453
Yeah well, I'm home now, Nuck.

31:54.487 --> 31:57.489
- So how about it?
- Had you stayed in school,

31:57.523 --> 31:59.792
it'd have been you
in that job and not Ryan.

31:59.826 --> 32:02.294
All right, so you're punishing me.
Is that it?

32:02.329 --> 32:04.713
- You're punishing me.
- I'm telling you to slow down,

32:04.748 --> 32:07.633
get the lay of the land.
You've been home now what? A month?

32:09.869 --> 32:12.204
Nucky, I'm not
the same kid that left.

32:15.475 --> 32:17.476
I've seen things.

32:17.510 --> 32:21.647
- I've done things. - Well, how are
we gonna keep you down on the farm?

32:21.681 --> 32:23.882
- I'm serious.
- I know.

32:25.268 --> 32:27.236
All right, look,

32:27.270 --> 32:29.221
that's 1,000 bucks.
Go buy yourself

32:29.239 --> 32:31.357
- a decent suit...
- I don't want your money!

32:31.391 --> 32:34.109
A fella hands you a grand,
you tell him to fuck himself?

32:34.160 --> 32:36.561
You're a pip, kid, I gotta say.

32:36.580 --> 32:40.199
Nucky, all I want
is an opportunity.

32:40.233 --> 32:43.452
This is America, ain't it?
Who the fuck's stopping you?

32:44.871 --> 32:47.506
Come on, let's go.

32:47.540 --> 32:50.626
- One for you.
- Two!

32:50.677 --> 32:54.046
- And two.
- Two pile of soups.

32:54.080 --> 32:56.382
And one for you.

32:59.052 --> 33:01.887
The automobile?

33:01.921 --> 33:04.023
Tell me again how you came
to find yourself

33:04.057 --> 33:06.442
getting chauffeured
around town.

33:07.611 --> 33:10.062
I told you.

33:10.096 --> 33:13.198
I was walking past the church
when I felt faint.

33:13.233 --> 33:14.933
Mr. Thompson saw me

33:14.951 --> 33:17.736
and was kind enough to have
his driver see me home.

33:20.606 --> 33:22.291
C'mere.

33:30.133 --> 33:32.384
You are a little warm.

33:34.087 --> 33:36.555
And you're feeling better
now though, are you?

33:36.589 --> 33:38.223
I am.

33:41.177 --> 33:43.012
And this?

33:43.063 --> 33:44.980
How did this find its way
under the mattress?

33:45.015 --> 33:47.632
- Mommy. - That money
belongs to the children.

33:47.651 --> 33:50.019
Like fuck it does!
Where'd you get it?

33:50.070 --> 33:52.521
- Huh?
- Never you mind where I got it.

33:52.572 --> 33:54.940
By whoring yourself out?

33:54.974 --> 33:57.409
You whore!

34:00.313 --> 34:02.748
- You gimme that money.
- No, you sit down

34:02.782 --> 34:04.750
or you'll get the belt!

34:08.588 --> 34:11.206
- Eat your food.
- I want mommy!

34:11.257 --> 34:14.176
Eat your food.

34:21.434 --> 34:23.052
Ahh.

34:23.103 --> 34:24.668
Ohh.

34:24.688 --> 34:26.505
Thank you.

34:28.975 --> 34:30.775
This is them.

34:32.779 --> 34:34.563
Gentlemen.

34:34.614 --> 34:36.899
Enoch Thompson.

34:36.949 --> 34:39.034
Okay.

34:39.069 --> 34:41.370
- Big Jim Colosimo.
- Mr. Thompasoni.

34:41.404 --> 34:43.237
- Nice to see you.
- Pleasure to meet you.

34:43.289 --> 34:45.741
Come on in.
Now if you come back here in July,

34:45.792 --> 34:47.859
at the pool they have
the sea nymph festival.

34:47.877 --> 34:50.695
- Seamina festival?
- You should come for that.

34:50.714 --> 34:52.880
- Got them.
- Like mermaids.

34:52.916 --> 34:55.167
January 16th,
it's 8:03 P.M.

34:55.201 --> 34:57.536
Johnny Torrio meeting
with Nucky Thompson.

34:57.554 --> 35:00.222
- Which one's Torrio?
- The gray tweed.

35:00.256 --> 35:02.474
"Gray tweed."

35:04.544 --> 35:07.546
We got a bead on Rothstein.
He just came in with Luciano.

35:07.564 --> 35:09.881
This other fellow
is big Jim Colosimo.

35:09.899 --> 35:12.067
- Come again?
- In the homburg.

35:12.102 --> 35:14.269
- The hamburg?
- The homburg.

35:14.320 --> 35:16.321
Never mind.
He took it off.

35:17.991 --> 35:19.942
- Who's this fella now?
- Who?

35:19.993 --> 35:21.994
- The guy in the brown suit.
- That's the concierge.

35:22.028 --> 35:25.864
- It's "Sierge"?
- The manager, he works here.

35:27.283 --> 35:30.035
So the red tie, that's big Jim?

35:31.171 --> 35:33.122
Does that man look big to you?

35:33.173 --> 35:35.740
- How's that?
- It's Arnold Rothstein.

35:35.759 --> 35:37.926
So it's not Colosimo?

35:37.961 --> 35:42.347
- Arnold Rothstein.
- And Nucky Luciano.

35:42.382 --> 35:43.682
- Lucky!
- Come again?

35:43.716 --> 35:46.468
Lucky Luciano, Nucky Thompson.

35:47.720 --> 35:51.256
So... who's Colosimo?

36:01.568 --> 36:03.619
Fella goes to divorce court.
The judge says

36:03.653 --> 36:05.988
"I've decided to give
your wife $25 a week."

36:06.039 --> 36:08.106
Fella says "that's mighty
swell of you, judge.

36:08.124 --> 36:10.609
I'll try to send her a few
clams myself now and again."

36:14.964 --> 36:16.548
- Clams?
- Money.

36:16.583 --> 36:19.051
Clams, money, capiro?

36:19.085 --> 36:21.220
Money, capiro?

36:21.254 --> 36:24.789
You should put it
in some lobster too, no?

36:26.792 --> 36:28.310
No!

36:28.344 --> 36:30.846
No no no.
None for me.

36:30.897 --> 36:32.797
You're a law-abiding
citizen, eh?

36:32.816 --> 36:34.933
- No, teetotaler.
Never touch it. - Oh.

36:34.967 --> 36:38.187
- He's the lightweight.
- I like to stay sharp at the tables.

36:38.238 --> 36:41.023
Yeah, sharp.
The way he wins, he wants to be sharp.

36:41.074 --> 36:44.827
Last year he clear $2 million just
f the world series alone, eh?

36:44.861 --> 36:47.812
- Two milliones.
- And they call that one lucky.

36:47.831 --> 36:50.032
What do you think
I'm sitting next to him for?

36:50.083 --> 36:52.618
Hey, boy, do you have
any Caruso records?

36:52.652 --> 36:55.370
- Enrico Caruso?
- That's fine.

36:55.421 --> 36:57.206
- Caruso, no?
- Go find some and play it.

36:57.257 --> 36:58.790
- Put it on, eh?
- Tell the boys.

36:58.824 --> 37:00.709
It's like funeral music here.

37:00.760 --> 37:02.827
How's the chow, fellas?

37:02.846 --> 37:04.546
- Fine.
- Delicious.

37:04.597 --> 37:06.665
Oh, ma, she's the best, eh?

37:06.683 --> 37:09.134
- You should come to my
restaurant sometime, eh? - Sure.

37:09.168 --> 37:12.187
I treat you nice, eh?
If you like to eat, you eat.

37:12.222 --> 37:14.439
If you don't like to eat...

37:15.775 --> 37:18.227
- Hmm?
- Who doesn't like to eat?

37:19.729 --> 37:22.064
Chicago's a fine town.

37:22.115 --> 37:23.782
It ain't New York,
that's for sure.

37:23.816 --> 37:25.651
New York ain't New York now
with prohibition.

37:25.685 --> 37:27.870
It will be if I have
something to say about it.

37:27.904 --> 37:29.988
Ain't that the reason
we're all here tonight?

37:32.358 --> 37:34.743
As you know, in light
of recent developments,

37:34.794 --> 37:37.629
I thought it might be of mutual
benefit for you boys to meet.

37:37.664 --> 37:40.582
All the way from chi-town out
of the goodness of his heart.

37:40.633 --> 37:43.051
When I say mutual benefit,
I mean mine too.

37:43.086 --> 37:45.053
I didn't come here
for the pastasciutta.

37:45.088 --> 37:48.507
I'll be expecting
a matchmaking fee.

37:48.541 --> 37:50.592
Of course.

37:50.643 --> 37:54.563
See, in addition to their other enterprises, Messrs.
Rothstein and Luciano

37:54.597 --> 37:58.016
have significant interests in the
cabaret business back in New York.

37:58.050 --> 37:59.735
And a man such as yourself,

37:59.769 --> 38:02.738
with both political influence as
well as a passing acquaintance

38:02.772 --> 38:04.823
with the seafaring types
of the Atlantic ocean...

38:04.857 --> 38:06.992
hey, Johnny, talk English.

38:08.444 --> 38:11.246
Salvatore...

38:12.165 --> 38:13.198
...Big business.

38:13.232 --> 38:15.167
So what's the difference?

38:19.255 --> 38:21.290
Go ahead, do what you
were going to do.

38:21.341 --> 38:23.908
Could you fix us up or no?

38:23.927 --> 38:27.129
We'll take alls we can get
up to 2,000 crates a month.

38:27.180 --> 38:29.348
For starters.

38:33.603 --> 38:35.220
You young fellas...

38:35.254 --> 38:37.806
no appreciation for
the art of conversation.

38:41.694 --> 38:43.445
All right, yeah, I gotta piss.

38:48.451 --> 38:49.868
I apologize.

38:49.902 --> 38:54.272
Ambition can be read
as impatience sometimes.

38:54.290 --> 38:56.625
- Arrogance too.
- Ehh...

38:58.795 --> 39:01.213
I have a friend...
a judge.

39:01.247 --> 39:03.415
His daughter's wedding
is in a week.

39:03.449 --> 39:07.002
I'd like to be able to accommodate
him and their 700 guests.

39:08.054 --> 39:09.554
- You haven't stockpiled?
- Mmmm.

39:09.589 --> 39:12.057
All sold already.
I'm coming up short.

39:13.793 --> 39:16.345
Well, I have a load
coming in tomorrow.

39:16.396 --> 39:18.680
500 crates Canadian club.

39:18.731 --> 39:21.850
Originally I'd planned to keep it,
but seeing how I'd like to start

39:21.901 --> 39:25.020
our relationship off on the right
foot, how about I let you have it?

39:25.071 --> 39:28.323
- How much?
- 60 grand for the entire load.

39:28.358 --> 39:30.826
But you use your own men
for the pickup.

39:39.952 --> 39:42.754
Send me over the details, we'll
settle up in cash tomorrow.

39:42.789 --> 39:44.489
All right.

39:44.507 --> 39:46.675
All right, gentlemen,

39:46.709 --> 39:48.660
- salut.
- Salut.

39:48.678 --> 39:49.928
Cheers.

39:49.962 --> 39:51.713
Cheers.

39:52.665 --> 39:54.933
I was in Chicago once.

39:54.967 --> 39:58.854
- Good steaks.
- It's all right.

39:58.888 --> 40:00.972
A little cold,
but so is Brooklyn.

40:01.006 --> 40:03.007
You get used to it, I guess.

40:03.026 --> 40:06.194
Summer of '17 I passed through
there on my way to camp Grant.

40:08.147 --> 40:09.781
Doughboy, huh?

40:09.816 --> 40:11.850
- Uh-huh.
- Me too.

40:11.868 --> 40:13.852
The lost battalion.

40:14.787 --> 40:16.071
No kidding.

40:17.690 --> 40:20.242
How about you?
You see any action?

40:20.293 --> 40:22.544
Little bit.

40:22.578 --> 40:25.247
Caught some shrapnel
from a Jerry's grenade.

40:25.298 --> 40:29.134
- Spent eight months in the hospital.
- Jesus.

40:32.672 --> 40:35.090
